Japan Should Honestly Admit Its Crimes and Apologize for Them 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Moscow, December 5 (KCNA) -- The 47th issue of the Russian paper Patriot published an article titled "'Treaty stained with human blood and peppered with lies" a century since the Japanese imperialists' fabrication of the "1905 Five-Point Treaty."
 The article recalled that the Japanese imperialists faked up the treaty in a brigandish manner on November 17, 1905 and announced it, thus using it for putting Korea under their military occupation and turning it into a colony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Explaining in detail how they fabricated the treaty, the article recalled that the more than 40 year-long colonial rule of the Japanese imperialists brought unspeakable misfortune and sufferings to the Korean people and turned Korea into a huge prison. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-Japanese guerrilla army commanded by President Kim Il Sung liberated Korea from Japanese militarism in 1945. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the U.S. imperialists occupied the southern half of Korea after the defeat of the Japanese imperialists. It has thus been under the U.S. colonial rule still today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has not yet apologized and compensated for the crimes committed by it during its colonial rule over Korea though six decades have passed since its defeat in the Second World War. On the contrary, it seeks to stage a comeback to Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It should honestly admit its past crimes and apologize for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan refuses to admit its past crimes, swimming against the trend of the times, it will never escape protest and denunciation from the international community.

All- People Rally Held in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- An all-people rally for defending national agriculture and winning legislation on the guarantee of rights to the part-timers reportedly took place in Maroni Park in Seoul on Dec 4.  
 It was attended by at least 8,000 workers, farmers, and youths and students affiliated to various organizations including the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions, the Federation of Peasants Associations, the Federation of Women Peasants Associations, the People's Solidarity and the People's Action against the Troop Dispatch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants declared that they would carry on their struggle till the south Korean authorities stop at once the opening of the rice market, guarantee rights to the part-timers and apologize for the farmer's death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally, they staged a demonstration. They assembled on Sejong Street  in Kwanghwamun after breaking through the cordon of the police which fired water cannons and flew helicopters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they held a candlelight function to mourn the death of farmer Jon Yong Chol. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, south Korean youths and students and members of civic and public organizations including the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification and the south Korean Alliance for Democracy and Reunification staged a surprise demonstration in front of Chongwadae in demand of the punishment of the police responsible for the death of Jon and the resignation of the government.

Immediate Halt to Anti-DPRK Smear Campaign Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification on Dec. 3 issued a commentary denouncing the U.S. and the ultra-right forces including the Grand National Party for their anti-DPRK campaign over its " human rights issue" that has reached an extreme phase. 
 The U.S. launched this offensive against the DPRK because their moves to pressurize it over the human rights issue and their strategy to establish military supremacy have come a cropper, the commentary noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the U.S. found its policy to isolate the DPRK unworkable, it began peddling the long bankrupt fiction of "human rights issue." The U.S. is not entitled to talk about someone's "human rights" as its history is woven with aggression and murder. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ultra-right forces including the GNP have been frantic in their offensive against the DPRK since the publication of the June 15 joint declaration. As the U.S. human rights campaign against the DPRK got evermore undisguised, they have joined in it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The anti-DPRK offensive over its "human rights issue" is nothing but the last resort of those on the death-beds. 
 It is necessary to frustrate the moves of the U.S. and ultra-right forces opposed to reunification through a decisive struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Intensive information service is required for laying bare the nature and ulterior aim of the U.S. offensive against the north over "its human rights issue." 
 The U.S. and ultra-right forces should immediately stop this campaign.

Mayor of Sankt-Petersburg of Russia Hosts Banquet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- Valentina Matvienko, mayor of Sankt-Petersburg of the Russian Federation, Tuesday hosted a banquet in connection with her visit to the DPRK. 
 She in her speech at the banquet said that brief as her stay in Korea was, she had opportunities to meet many Korean friends to exchange views on the issue of boosting the cooperation in trade between the two countries and its prospect, expressing her hope that the visit of her and her party to the DPRK would make a positive contribution to the development of the political and trade ties between Russia and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing her gratitude to the Korean friends for the kind and cordial hospitality accorded to them, she expressed the hope that the cooperation in trade between Sankt-Petersburg and the DPRK would become more brisk in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, in his speech said that the bilateral agreements and projects to implement them would be energetically pushed forward in the future to reap shining results. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the mayor and her party made a significant contribution to promoting the development of the Russia-DPRK relations during their visit to the DPRK, he wholeheartedly wished the Russian people greater success in their work to make fresh progress in the development of Sankt-Petersburg and build powerful Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Ryang Man Gil, chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, Kung Sok Ung, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade Kim Yong Jae who is chairman of the Korean Committee for the Promotion of International Trade, Vice-Chairperson of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Hong Son Ok who is chairperson of the DPRK-Russia Friendship Association, Ri Ho Hyon, chairman of the Nampho City People's Committee, and officials concerned. The mayor's party, Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Gennadiyevich Karlov and staff members of the embassy were present there.

Japanese Heavyweight's Ridiculous Remarks Flayed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- Some days ago the KEDO decided to totally stop the construction of the light water reactors (LWRs) for the DPRK, as dictated by the United States. In the wake of the announcement of this decision Chief Cabinet Secretary of Japan Abe insisted that "north Korea compensate for the financial loss."
 Rodong Sinmun Wednesday observes in a signed commentary in this regard: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The illogical and unreasonable remarks made by Abe clearly prove that Japan is no more than a political waiting maid and diplomatic servant for the U.S.
 It is the deeply rooted tendency and bad habit of Japan to blindly toe the U.S. line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has every right to demand compensation for the losses caused by the stoppage of the LWR construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the 1994 DPRK-U.S. Agreed Framework (AF) the U.S. was obliged to build two LWRs and provide them to the DPRK by the year 2003 in return for its freeze of nuclear facilities and supply 500,000 tons of heavy fuel oil to it on an annual basis till the construction was completed. It also assured the DPRK that it would not threaten the latter with nukes. However, the U.S. had not properly implemented any of its commitments till the deadline for the LWR construction fixed in the AF. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has totally scrapped the AF and stopped the construction, causing huge political and economic losses to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is, however, working hard to shift the responsibility for "compensation" on to the DPRK by falsifying truth. This behavior only discloses Japan's short-sighted politics and its true colors as a political waiting maid for the U.S. as it is keen to gain even small profits by serving it. 
 Japan is not entitled to demand the DPRK compensate for the above-said losses nor is it in a position to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It would be well advised to clearly understand the issue with reason and stop acting a humiliating political waiting maid for the U.S.

Mayor of Sankt-Petersburg Interviewed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- Valentina Matvienko, mayor of Sankt-Petersburg, was interviewed in Pyongyang on Dec. 6.
 On hand were KCNA reporters and the press corps accompanying the mayor. 
 She, answering the questions put by reporters, said that while touring different parts of the DPRK, she was deeply impressed to see the Korean people working hard to build a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She noted that there was a frank exchange of views on bilateral cooperation in different fields including economy and foreign trade and a series of relevant documents were signed at meetings and talks held during her stay in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The friendly relations between Russia and the DPRK are favorably developing under the deep care of President Putin and leader Kim Jong Il, she said, adding that she would make every effort to boost the bilateral friendly and cooperative relations in the future.

Pro-U.S. Conservative Forces' Anti-North Campaign Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- The clan of the Grand National Party of south Korea is busy creating an atmosphere of confrontation with the north, vociferating about a "bill" and "resolution" at the "National Assembly" by zealously joining foreign forces in their smear campaign against the DPRK over its "human rights issue." They have become all the more frantic in their fascist moves to crack down on the forces for the reunification movement under the signboard of "preserving the nature of the system." Worse still, new conservative forces that have emerged under the patronage of the United States are closing their ranks, blaring the pro-U.S. and anti-north trumpets. 
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun today says in a signed article: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces of south Korea are persisting in their moves for confrontation and war against the north while talking about "cooperation" with outside forces. This is an unpardonable treacherous criminal act in the June 15 era of reunification as it is a vicious challenge to the Korean nation's cause of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. sycophantic traitors of south Korea ignited a war in league with the U.S. imperialists in the 1950s, worked hard to unleash a war against the north while vociferating about "march north to unify" with the backing of the U.S. imperialists after the war. They became evermore undisguised in their moves for confrontation with the north during the "Yusin" dictatorship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces including the GNP based on pro-U.S. flunkeyism and confrontation with the north are following in the steps of their preceding pro-U.S. sycophantic traitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No sooner had the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration been published  than the U.S. imperialists openly deterred the Koreans from pooling their efforts for fear that  south Korea might slip out of their hands. The U.S. pressurized south Korea to deal with the issue of inter-Korean relations as intended by it, asserting that south Korea should pursue its policy toward the north with the approval of the U.S. and strictly observe the principles of reciprocity and verification. Meanwhile, the U.S. blustered that it would not rule out even a military attack on the DPRK, raising a hue and cry over "missile threat" and "threat of biological and chemical weapons" of the DPRK and listing it as part of an "axis of evil". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces of south Korea are playing an active role as a shock force in the implementation of the U.S. policy to isolate and stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The Korean nation will certainly force the south Korean pro-U.S. conservative forces of south Korea to pay for their criminal acts of opposing the fellow countrymen and obstructing the reunification of the country, insisting on "cooperation" with foreign forces.

RS on Tremendous Vitality of Songun Politics 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) --The justice of the Songun politics and its tremendous vitality lie in that it is the socialist political mode making it possible to give fullest play to the ideological and moral might of the revolutionary ranks. 
 Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed article. It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ideology serves as a lifeline in carrying out the socialist cause and the politics that regards the ideological work as a cornerstone of revolution is an ever-victorious one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK could emerge victorious in the two revolutionary wars fought against the formidable enemies of imperialism and has won victory after victory at different stages of social revolution without failures and turns and twists. This was possible thanks to the great idea of the leaders and the firm faith and will of the army and people in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics is, in essence, a political mode, an organic combination of the politics of putting main emphasis on the idea of the revolutionary army, the idea of attaching importance to the ideology, and the idea of giving priority to military affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics helps the popular masses fully display the might of ideology because it is the most popular political mode for arming all of them with correct guidelines in our era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary ranks are solidly united in thinking and purpose on the basis of the Songun idea. As a result, the servicepersons and people are demonstrating their dignity as the army and people strong in independence and bringing about the  greatest successes in the efforts to attain national prosperity despite any stern ordeals without hesitation, vacillation and pessimism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il created the most powerful and ideal political mode in the present era by combining the Juche-oriented theory of ideology with philosophy on the army. This is a great immortal exploit performed by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics serves as a revolutionary banner for placing the political and ideological features of the revolutionary ranks on highest level in the era. 
 The might of the Songun politics represents the might of the revolutionary soldier spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The creation of the revolutionary soldier spirit has put the  ideological and moral traits of the revolutionary ranks on the highest plane.
 Kim Jong Il ushered in a new era in which the ideological and moral traits of the whole society are modeled after the ideology and spirit of the revolutionary army. This is an outstanding feat performed by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics serves as a powerful treasured sword as it brings about fresh innovation and leap forward in building a great prosperous powerful nation by dint of the political work aimed at gripping the hearts of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cause of socialism advances by dint of ideology and emerges victorious by dint of faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The army and people of the DPRK will hold fast to the great Songun politics for giving fullest play to the might of ideology as an ever-victorious treasured sword and thus effect steady leap forward in the efforts to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation of Juche, the article concludes.

Arthroscope-aided Operation Method Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- A treatment team of Pyongyang University of Medicine has succeeded in operating on injured joints with the help of arthroscope without incising.
 By the method, two holes for a micro-camera and special tools are made on the damaged part. The joint is screened on TV sets for operation. And a sort of liquid is injected into the part to make a room for operation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The method was initially developed for the purpose of diagnosis but now is used mainly for surgery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It gives fewer burdens to patients, leaves no a big operation mark and has not sequelae. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
By the method the team enucleated arthrophytes at first, but now carries on such difficult operations such as meniscus excision and joint-mice extirpation.
 It has reduced the operation time from four-five hours to one and a half hours. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The team is deepening its research to do more complex operations

National Sketch Festival in Brisk Preparations
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA) -- The First National Sketch Festival for Celebrating February 16 (birthday of leader Kim Jong Il) will be held at the Pyongyang International House of Culture from February 2, Juche 95 (2006) to 28.
 More than 1,000 sketch works are expected to be displayed at the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival will be attended not only by artists but by art amateurs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon receiving the news of the festival, artists, working youth and students across the country are making their best to create sketch works.
 The Art Department of the Ministry of Culture is making all necessary preparations for the festival in close contact with the Central Committee of the    Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League and the cultural departments of provincial people's committees. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Youth League Central Committee notified guidelines of the festival to its interiors and is making preparations to hold 15-day regional sketch contests.
 The Juvenile Extracurricular Education Guidance Bureau had already organized a sketch contest at the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace in October last. It was participated in by over 360 art circle members from some 160 units of the country including schoolchildren's palaces and students' halls. And the selected works are being given final touches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Regional sketch contests were held in provinces in October and November. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In North Hwanghae and North Hamgyong Provinces sketch contests were held for tens of days amid deep interests of local people. They produced fine sketch works high in ideological and artistic standard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, creators and art experts including those of the Mansudae Art Studio, Central Fine Arts Company, Pyongyang University of Fine Arts and other units are striving hard to depict better features of the people enjoying a happy life full of hope in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first national sketch festival will demonstrate the emotional life of the Korean people and inspire the servicepersons and people in the efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation.

North-South Talks on Sports
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kaesong, December 8 (KCNA) -- North-south talks on sports were held in Kaesong today.
 At the talks both sides shared the understanding that it conforms with the basic spirit of the June 15 joint declaration for the north and the south to form a unified team to participate in major international games to be held in future on the principle of contributing to national reconciliation, unity and reunification in the idea of "By our nation itself" and had sincere discussions about it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They agreed to continue discussing technical issues related to the formation of the unified team. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the talks were Vice-Chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission Ri Tong Ho, Vice-Chairman of the south Korean Olympic Committee Pak Song In and other officials concerned of the north and the south.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 7 (KCNA)- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, inspected KPA Unit 744 honored with the title of O Jung Hup-led seventh regiment. 
 He was saluted on the spot by commanding officers of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After acquainting himself with the unit's performance of duty, he looked round the room devoted to its history, conducted by its commander. 
 He dropped in at the servicepersons' hall to learn about how the political work and entertainment are conducted for them. It is a great success that the unit has built a modern hall on its own, he said, underscoring the need to minutely run the hall so that they may fully enjoy a cultural life.
 He watched soldiers undergoing training in the combined drill ground of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed satisfaction over the fact that the unit is training officers and men as a-match-for-a hundred stalwart fighters by successfully building modern drill ground to suit the content and nature of training and widely applying the latest apparatuses to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called on all units to pay primary attention to the combat and political training, noting that intensified combat training provides a basic way of bolstering the strength of the matchless army and the master key to training the soldiers as a-match-for-a hundred fighters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round the compound of the barracks, he learned about the unit's management. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching the compound of the barracks and their surroundings that match well the compound kept spick-and-span, he said this is fantastic scenery which can be seen in the era of Songun. He highly praised the servicepersons of the unit for having radically changed the appearance of the unit in a few years. 
 The commanding officers of the unit have energetically pushed forward the command and management of the unit, considering it as a basic work to organize and command the implementation of the military and political tasks before the unit, thus bringing about shining fruits as we see today, he said, adding that great miracles are reported from various places as the hearts of the soldiers are beating high with the revolutionary spirit of carrying out the orders in a do-or-die spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He made the rounds of a mess hall, a kitchen, a vegetable store, a food processing room and other supply service facilities and a nursery. He appreciated the work style of the commanding officers of the unit, saying he could see the tenacious way of managing its economic life through every supply service facility kept in good shape. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated once again the achievements made by the unit, saying the unit has accumulated a wealth of precious experience in the combat and political training, its management and in all other aspects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Hwang Pyong So, vice department director of the C.C.,WPK.
